RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250, if for $5,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHAYMYNAME moved straight to the front setting the pace off the rail, faced mild pressure up the backstretch, regained a clear advantage again on the far turn, drifted out in upper stretch and lugged out near the sixteenth pole but held while being kept to the task. PEACE PACT settled off the pace in the two path, raced inside foes up the backstretch into the far turn, was encouraged along three furlongs out, kept on inside to get the nod for second. EXAGERADORA broke a step slowly, settled at the rear off the rail, advanced outside foes three to four wide up the backstretch, moved between runners at the quarter pole, drifted out through the stretch and was outfinished for second. PAUL'S TRICKY TALE chased briefly two to three wide, steadily dropped back between runners up the backstretch, tired. MEMORIES ETERNAL switched out and moved forward pressing briefly up the backstretch from outside, began to drop back three to four wide on the far turn, tired.

ENTRY.COMMENT: switched out, brief press, 3-4w 2nd turn, tired

ENTRY.COMMENT: inside, encouraged 3/8, got 2nd

ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, off rail, drift & lug out str, held
